nt. It is a kind of new Operating System for the modern Web 2.0 users which is totally powered by Google Apps and Web 2.0 Apps and introduces the concept of using the Web for everything.\r\n\r\ngOS Rocket 2.0 was recently released at the Consumer Electronics Show 2008 and is now available to download for free.\r\n\r\ngOS works perfectly on low specification computers as it uses very little amount of RAM and processing speed. It highly depends on Web 2.0 and Ajax web technology and almost all applications on the gOS are web based.\r\n\r\ngOS Rocket also comes integrated with Google Gears, which suggests that in the future the on-line google applications can be used while off-line.\r\n\r\nThe primary UI of gOS has a Mac OSX Leapord-like Dock menu called the iBar which features icons for the following Google applications and services:\r\n\r\nGoogle Mail \r\nGoogle News \r\nGoogle Calendar \r\nGoogle Maps \r\nGoogle Docs \r\nGoogle Products \r\nMeebo \r\nYouTube \r\nBlogger \r\nFaceBook \r\nWikipedia", "imagename": "2bd2fff596e447d88e424b2aa5b8f41d.jpg", "infoid": 44214, "category": "technology_web2", "isanchordig": 1, "ischecked": 0, "isdelete": 0, "categoryclass": "technology", "via": null, "real_tags": ["web2.0"]}, {"url": "http://mail.qq.com/m", "title": "QQ\u90ae\u7bb1\u652f\u6301IPhone", "tags": "qq\u90ae\u7bb1 qq iphone ", "name": "cacard", "posttime": "2008-01-21 22:38:15", "ip": "222.178.10.246", "mark": 3, "note": "http://mail.qq.com/m\uff0c\u5e94\u8be5\u662fQQMail\u4e3a\u667a\u80fd\u624b\u673a\u7684\u5165\u53e3\uff0c\u4f60\u5982\u679c\u4f7f\u7528\u7684IPhone\uff0c\u4e5f\u53ef\u4ee5\u901a\u8fc7\u8fd9\u4e2a\u5730\u5740\u8bbf\u95ee\u4e86~~", "imagename": "3c37f12ac1914b6daaee1dc08a6784af.gif", "infoid": 44213, "category": "technology_web2", "isanchordig": 1, "ischecked": 0, "isdelete": 0, "categoryclass": "technology", "via": null, "real_tags": ["qq\u90ae\u7bb1", "qq", "iphone"]}]